        <p class="cluster-kicker">What most teams build</p>
        <h2>Pipelines are not clusters.</h2>
        <p>
          Most AI systems today are built like assembly lines. Input goes in. One agent
          processes it. Then another. Then another. That model works for simple automations:
          generate a blog, summarize a meeting, route a ticket.
        </p>
        <p>
          Enterprise software projects are not linear. They involve parallel workstreams,
          shared context, role specialization, dependencies, review systems, human checkpoints,
          conflicting priorities, iteration loops, scaling workloads, and long-running coordination.
        </p>
      </div>

